   CVN-BUSH (Cincinnati, Ohio) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush
campaigns in Ohio on his way to the Republican National Convention
in Philadelphia. Bush says he and his running mate, former Defense
Secretary Dick Cheney, plan to operate as a ``tag team'' in such
battleground states as Ohio, taking turns campaigning here. By
STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   CVN-McCAIN-REFORM (Philadelphia) _ Sen. John McCain brings his
reform message to Philadelphia on the eve of the Republican
National Convention, telling cheering supporters to ``keep
fighting, keep fighting'' for campaign finance reform. McCain said
the Democrats are the party of ```the status quo'' while the
Republicans are the ``party of reform.'' By TIMOTHY SPENCE.
</P>
<P>
   CVN-MICHIGAN (Philadelphia) _ State Sen. Bill Schuette of
Midland, one of 58 Michigan delegates to the Republican Natonal
Convention, arrives here today and discusses his views of the GOP
ticket and platform in an interview. Earlier, U.S. Rep. Dave Camp,
U.S. Sen. Spencer Abraham and Michigan Gov. John Engler said the
party will carry the state handily. By ERIC ROSENBERG.
</P>
