if there is not enough heat to go around. In Oakland, 10 minutes
over the Bay Bridge, it is 10 degrees warmer, with the sun a notch
brighter and the breeze as light as baby's breath. And for every 10
miles inland from San Francisco, the conventional wisdom goes, the
weather gets warmer and warmer. Yet San Franciscans worth their
chest-thumping civic pride are proud of this paradise of perpetual
spring. By Evelyn Nieves.
