<P>
   GOP-PROTESTS (Philadelphia) _ The largest of the dissent
protests, Unity 2000, occupies Sunday as the conventioneers settle
in and marchers vie for media time, wending through the city. Unity
2000 is an umbrella group of everything from NOW to NAACP. The
self-styled anarchist demonstrators will come later in the week.
City police are well restrained, even amiable so far, in the hands
of Commissioner Timoney, an ex-New Yorker, who is riding in his
bike helmet and shorts with motorcycle police as the best way to
monitor things. ``So far so good; but it's early, and you never get
cocky,'' he said as the police adjusted to such ad hoc marchers as
the 200 teens loudly devoted to the cause of virginity. (''Free sex
kills!'' ``Pure and Proud!'') 1000 words. By Francis X. Clines.
