most ever paid to a player who was drafted by any team.
</P>
<P>
   Tampa Bay gave pitcher Matt White a $10.2-million bonus, and
Arizona gave Travis Lee a $10-million deal and pitcher John
Patterson a $6-million check. But in each of those cases, the
drafted players were declared free agents after using loopholes.
....
