THIS WEEK'S TV HIGHLIGHTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TODAY: To accommodate ABC News' coverage of the Republican
National Convention,the network was given the power to move the
kickoff of tonight's Hall of Fame exhibition from Canton, Ohio, up
an hour. Nice set-up for Dennis Miller's first rant in his ``MNF''
debut - a free shot at Cokie Roberts. NFL exhibition: Hall of Fame
Game, San Francisco vs. New England, Channel 7, 4 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   TUESDAY: Take the day off and head down to Del Mar. But first,
in honor of Groucho, set up the VCR for ... ``A Day At the Races,''
Turner Classic Movies, 7 p.m.
