 (EDS: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Sunday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.) 
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-DANCE-LINCOLN-FESTIVAL-NYT (moved Wednesday, July 26)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, July 26
about the Lincoln Center Out of Doors festival misstates its
closing date and the tenure of Jenneth Webster as artistic
director. The festival ends on Aug. 27, not 29; Webster has been
there 11 years, not 20.
</P>
<P>
   The article also misstates the occupation of a performer, Ali
Akbar Khan. He is a sarod player, not a singer.  &QL; 
